      <p>
        <s>The drama extract <ref target="c12gk3_1" type="scene">Act 1, Scene 7</ref> from the drama <ref target="c12gk3_1" type="title">Macbeth</ref> by <ref target="c12gk3_1" type="author">Shakespeare</ref> is about <choice><orig>a</orig><reg>an</reg></choice> argument between <ref target="c12gk3_1" type="character">Macbeth</ref> and <ref target="c12gk3_1" type="character">Lady Macbeth</ref>.</s>
      </p>
      <p>
        <s>They are talking about the plan to kill <ref target="c12gk3_1" type="character">Duncan</ref>.</s>
        <s><ref target="c12gk3_1" type="character">Duncan</ref> is the King of <name type="geo">Scotland</name>.</s>
        <s>He has two sons.</s>
        <s>They want to kill <ref target="c12gk3_1" type="character">King Duncan</ref> so that <ref target="c12gk3_1" type="character">Macbeth</ref> can become King of <name type="geo">Scotland</name>.</s>
        <s><ref target="c12gk3_1" type="character">Macbeth</ref> is unsure about the plan.</s>
        <s>He <choice><orig>think</orig><reg>thinks</reg></choice> that he <choice><orig>have</orig><reg>has</reg></choice> earned a high reputation from the people <ref target="c12gk3_1" type="line">(l. 3f.)</ref> and <choice><orig>ask</orig><reg>asks</reg></choice> what happened if they fail <ref target="c12gk3_1" type="line">(l. 38)</ref>.</s>
        <s>But <ref target="c12gk3_1" type="character">Lady Macbeth</ref> has a different <choice><orig>oppinion</orig><reg>opinion</reg></choice> about this topic.</s>
        <s>She <choice><orig>think</orig><reg>thinks</reg></choice> that it is a good plan to kill <ref target="c12gk3_1" type="character">Duncan</ref> while he sleeps <ref target="c12gk3_1" type="line">(l. 41)</ref>.</s>
        <s>First they get <ref target="c12gk3_1" type="character"><choice><orig>Duncans</orig><reg>Duncan's</reg></choice></ref> two chamberlains very drunk and <choice><orig>than</orig><reg>then</reg></choice> they could kill <ref target="c12gk3_1" type="character">Duncan</ref> easily <ref target="c12gk3_1" type="line">(l. 43)</ref>.</s>
      </p>
